law.text:
As used in KRS 439.590 to 439.630, unless the context otherwise requires:
"Secretary" means the secretary of the Justice and Public Safety Cabinet;
"Commissioner" means the commissioner of the Department of Corrections;
"Department" means the Department of Corrections;
"Facility" means the community correctional center; and
"Relative" means a spouse; child, including stepchild, adopted child, or child as to whom the prisoner, though not a biological parent, has acted in the place of a parent; parent including a person who, though not a biological parent, has acted in the place of a parent; brother; sister; or grandparents.
